why were there different german army corps and divisions during ww what did they typically comprise of in terms of various fighting components the ii ss panzer corps at the rd battle of kharkov and kursk was composed of the 'classic' ss divisions lah das reich totenkopf also attached was the independent nd heavy tank battalion while the th and th ss divisions were assigned to the ii ss panzer corps during normandy and operation market garden battles later in the war the divisions and battalions didn't always stay with the corps but were reassigned throughout the course of the war this gives you an idea of what a corps was composed of hodgepodge of divisions and battalions Leibstandarte SS Adolf Hitler SS Division Totenkopf SS Division (motorised) Wiking Eastern Front (World War II) II SS Panzer Corps Grossdeutschland Division Battle of Kursk Operation Market Garden Battle of Normandy 5th SS Volunteer Sturmbrigade Wallonien German 4th Panzer Division 6th SS Volunteer Sturmbrigade Langemarck Erich von Manstein Battle of the Bulge German Panzer Lehr Division Hasso von Manteuffel Fritz Witt Waffen-SS Third Battle of Kharkov German XLVIII Panzer Corps Blitzkrieg Irish Guards U.S. 82nd Airborne Division Battle of Kock (1939) Second Battle of El Alamein British 1st Airborne Division Hyazinth Graf Strachwitz von Gross-Zauche und Camminetz World War II German Army Battle of France Kurt Meyer (Panzermeyer) Battle of Stalingrad 4th SS Volunteer Panzergrenadier Brigade Nederland Battle of Brze____ Litewski British Expeditionary Force 12th SS Panzer Division Hitlerjugend 9th SS Panzer Division Hohenstaufen 20th Waffen Grenadier Division of the SS (1st Estonian) Royal Marines Franz B__ke German III Corps Battle of Berlin 17th SS Panzergrenadier Division G__tz von Berlichingen German First Panzer Army 6th SS Mountain Division Nord 11th SS Volunteer Panzergrenadier Division Nordland Kamenets-Podolsky Pocket Fallschirm-Panzer Division 1 Hermann G__ring Structure of the British Army 